The latter part of this volume, like the other, consists of the charters and writs of the Bishoprick, of date subsequent to the period at which the previous part was copied, and for the most part entered at the time of the transactions they record.

The first half of each volume of these records of the See may be said generally to record the growth and acquisitiones the Church property3 while the latter part of both relates to its dismemberment and total alienation.
